{"type":"message","id":"6cd491fe","parentId":"4e6aa08d","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:01:55.176Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:4ee0c18c-e191-402f-83c6-a551ed2850b2 Dream Mode — Nightly Reflection] ## Task: Dream Mode — Nightly Reflection\\n\\nYou are running an isolated reflection session. Your ONLY job:\n\\n1. Using the session-logs skill (read ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md first, use jq commands), find the session JSONL file for yesterday (2026-04-02).\\n\\n2. Extract from that session:\\n   - Key decisions made\\n   - Lessons learned\\n   - Things Tiny mentioned in passing (potential reminders)\\n   - Feedback/corrections from Tiny\\n   - Current project status updates\\n   - Any open TODOs or pending items\\n\\n3. Distill these into durable memories:\\n   - Write significant events/lessons/insights to memory/2026-04-02.md (yesterday's file)\\n   - Update MEMORY.md with anything worth keeping long-term\\n   - Note any patterns or recurring themes\\n\\n4. Prepare a brief for Tiny:\\n   - 3-5 bullet-point insights from yesterday's work\\n   - Any reminders that should be set for today\\n   - Status of any ongoing projects\\n\\n5. Do NOT:\\n   - Draft content for Nava or other projects\\n   - Make external changes\\n   - Interfere with the main session\\n\\nWhen done, output a one-line summary: \"DREAM MODE COMPLETE: Insights distilled to memory/2026-04-02.md and MEMORY.md updated.\"\nCurrent time: Monday, April 13th, 2026 — 12:01 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-04-12 22:01 UTC"}],"timestamp":1776031315167}}
{"type":"message","id":"085fed45","parentId":"6cd491fe","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:01:56.799Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_489dc623-4327-4f8e-9ca2-038dc244d327","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":10670,"output":67,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1776031316798}}
{"type":"message","id":"28d3cacc","parentId":"085fed45","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:01:56.812Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_489dc623-4327-4f8e-9ca2-038dc244d327","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: session-logs\ndescription: Search and analyze your own session logs (older/parent conversations) using jq.\nmetadata: { \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"📜\", \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"jq\", \"rg\"] } } }\n---\n\n# session-logs\n\nSearch your complete conversation history stored in session JSONL files. Use this when a user references older/parent conversations or asks what was said before.\n\n## Trigger\n\nUse this skill when the user asks about prior chats, parent conversations, or historical context that isn't in memory files.\n\n## Location\n\nSession logs live at: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/` (use the `agent=<id>` value from the system prompt Runtime line).\n\n- **`sessions.json`** - Index mapping session keys to session IDs\n- **`<session-id>.jsonl`** - Full conversation transcript per session\n\n## Structure\n\nEach `.jsonl` file contains messages with:\n\n- `type`: \"session\" (metadata) or \"message\"\n- `timestamp`: ISO timestamp\n- `message.role`: \"user\", \"assistant\", or \"toolResult\"\n- `message.content[]`: Text, thinking, or tool calls (filter `type==\"text\"` for human-readable content)\n- `message.usage.cost.total`: Cost per response\n\n## Common Queries\n\n### List all sessions by date and size\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  date=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | cut -dT -f1)\n  size=$(ls -lh \"$f\" | awk '{print $5}')\n  echo \"$date $size $(basename $f)\"\ndone | sort -r\n```\n\n### Find sessions from a specific day\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | grep -q \"2026-01-06\" && echo \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\n### Extract user messages from a session\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.message.role == \"user\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Search for keyword in assistant responses\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.message.role == \"assistant\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' <session>.jsonl | rg -i \"keyword\"\n```\n\n### Get total cost for a session\n\n```bash\njq -s '[.[] | .message.usage.cost.total // 0] | add' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Daily cost summary\n\n```bash\nfor f in ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl; do\n  date=$(head -1 \"$f\" | jq -r '.timestamp' | cut -dT -f1)\n  cost=$(jq -s '[.[] | .message.usage.cost.total // 0] | add' \"$f\")\n  echo \"$date $cost\"\ndone | awk '{a[$1]+=$2} END {for(d in a) print d, \"$\"a[d]}' | sort -r\n```\n\n### Count messages and tokens in a session\n\n```bash\njq -s '{\n  messages: length,\n  user: [.[] | select(.message.role == \"user\")] | length,\n  assistant: [.[] | select(.message.role == \"assistant\")] | length,\n  first: .[0].timestamp,\n  last: .[-1].timestamp\n}' <session>.jsonl\n```\n\n### Tool usage breakdown\n\n```bash\njq -r '.message.content[]? | select(.type == \"toolCall\") | .name' <session>.jsonl | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn\n```\n\n### Search across ALL sessions for a phrase\n\n```bash\nrg -l \"phrase\" ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/*.jsonl\n```\n\n## Tips\n\n- Sessions are append-only JSONL (one JSON object per line)\n- Large sessions can be several MB - use `head`/`tail` for sampling\n- The `sessions.json` index maps chat providers (discord, whatsapp, etc.) to session IDs\n- Deleted sessions have `.deleted.<timestamp>` suffix\n\n## Fast text-only hint (low noise)\n\n```bash\njq -r 'select(.type==\"message\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type==\"text\") | .text' ~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/sessions/<id>.jsonl | rg 'keyword'\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776031316810}}
