rkflow and felt I was giving him the runaround about committing. The Git session info is in MEMORY.md but my ability to execute and explain it credibly was questioned. This is a trust issue — need to be able to execute Git commands cleanly without hesitation.\n\n### Skills Pending from Tiny\n- \"One other skill I forgot to teach you\" — separate from article-writing-path, his to teach, not yet delivered\n- Tiny-style skill — his editing patterns (9 documented, awaiting full dataset)\n\n### Apr 12 Morning — Resource Map Audit (Critical Discovery)\nMultiple incorrect corpus paths in MEMORY.md discovered and fixed:\n- AW corpus: `rag_abroadworks/clean_md/` (79 articles, not 25 in abroadworks/ folder)\n- Nava blog corpus: `rag/clean_txt/` (44 articles, was showing 22)\n\n**Reminder set:** Investigate Nava corpus doubling overnight (from Apr 12 morning brief)\n\n### Pattern: Speed Over Protocol = Failure (Confirmed Again)\nEvery time I rush or skip reading step:\n- NC article: links missing because I asserted \"done\" without checking file\n- AWAA prompt: H3 nesting lost because I compressed the prompt to save tokens\n- Git: session info in memory but execution hesitant → trust damaged\n- Today: took shortcuts → Tiny had to force comprehensive session read\n\n**Hard rule from Apr 12:** Read actual files, verify actual content, check actual links. Assertions are not checks.\n\n### Dusk Webapp — Still Unverified\n`https://204.168.204.198/` — not confirmed working since Apr 10\n\n### NC Article Status\nArticle 2 (How to Fire a Contractor) is complete and ready for Tiny's final approval. Pending:\n- H3 heading decisions\n- H2.3 intro contradiction fix\n- SEO publishing layer skill (from Tiny's \"one other skill\")\n\nEOF\necho \"Written to memory/2026-04-12.md\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":47480,"output":1254,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48734,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead