{"type":"message","id":"ee82a3e4","parentId":"61194def","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:06:42.452Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_79958c2a-55e6-45e0-b045-100a7c6e386c","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"### Git Workflow Gap — CRITICAL (Apr 12)\nTiny asked about Git workflow and felt I was giving him the runaround about committing. The Git session info is in MEMORY.md but my ability to execute and explain it credibly was questioned. This is a trust issue — need to be able to execute Git commands cleanly without hesitation.\n\n**Hard rule (Apr 12):** When Tiny asks about Git, do it. Not \"here's how\" — just do it.\n\n### Git/Backup Recon Task — CRITICAL (Apr 12, Still Pending)\n> \"I want you to go to every backup folder and every file in your workspace. I need you to read every single session you and I have ever had.\"\n\nGiven at 20:54 Apr 12. NOT YET DONE. Must be completed before next session. This is Tiny's explicit instruction given in frustration after multiple shortcut failures. Read all session files, document findings, no shortcuts.\n\n### Resource Map Audit — Critical Corrections (Apr 12 Morning)\nMultiple incorrect corpus paths in MEMORY.md discovered and fixed:\n- AW corpus: `rag_abroadworks/clean_md/` (79 articles, correct)\n- Nava blog corpus: `rag/clean_txt/` (44 articles, correct)\n\n**Pattern:** My memory of corpus sizes was wrong. Always verify against actual directory counts, not memory assertions.\n\n### Pattern: Speed Over Protocol = Failure (Confirmed Again — Apr 12)\nEvery shortcut taken today:\n- NC article: links missing because I asserted \"done\" without file check\n- AWAA prompt: H3 nesting lost because I compressed to save tokens\n- Git: session info in memory but execution hesitant\n- Session read: shortcuts → Tiny forced comprehensive file read\n\n**Hard rule (Apr 12):** Read actual files. Verify actual content. Check actual links. Assertions are not checks.\n\n### Skills Pending from Tiny (Apr 12)\n- \"One other skill I forgot to teach you\" — his to teach, separate from article-writing-path\n- Tiny-style skill — 9 editing patterns documented, awaiting full dataset\n\n### Tiny's Core Critique (Apr 12)\n> \"You are basically getting in your own way. You are creating the problems you you are then trying to solve.\"\n\n**What he rejected:** promises, retrospectives, plans to improve\n**What he asked for:** Minimum viable next step\n\n---\n\n## AntiGravity = Dawn Webapp Template (Apr 9)","old_string":"## AntiGravity = Dawn Webapp Template (Apr 9)","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":48119,"output":589,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48708,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1776031602451}}
